1 AMEND House Amendment No._____ to House Bill No. 2167, Page 1, Line 14, by deleting
2 said line and inserting in lieu thereof the following:
3
4 ""311.630. 1. The supervisor of alcohol and tobacco control and employees to be
5 selected and designated as peace officers by the supervisor of alcohol and tobacco control are
6 hereby declared to be peace officers of the state of Missouri, with full power and authority to
7 make arrests and searches and seizures only for violations of the provisions of this chapter
8 relating to intoxicating liquors, [and] sections 407.924 to 407.934 relating to tobacco products,
9 or when exigent circumstances that present an immediate threat of bodily harm to any person
10 exist, and to serve any process connected with the enforcement of such laws. The peace officers
11 so designated shall have been previously appointed and qualified under the provisions of section
12 311.620 and shall be required to hold a valid peace officer license pursuant to chapter 590.
13 2. The supervisor of alcohol and tobacco control shall furnish such peace officers with
14 credentials showing their authority and a special badge, which they shall carry on their person at
15 all times while on duty. The names of the peace officers so designated shall be made a matter of
16 public record in the office of the supervisor of alcohol and tobacco control.
17 3. All fees for the arrest and transportation of persons arrested and for the service of
18 writs and process shall be the same as provided by law in criminal proceedings and shall be
19 taxed as costs.
20 320.230. 1. The state fire marshal shall conduct investigations and may conduct
21 hearings into the cause, origin, or circumstances of fire losses and shall cooperate with the
22 appropriate fire or police officials of this state or its political subdivisions in investigations of the
23 cause, origin or circumstances of fires, explosions or related occurrences involving the
24 possibility of arson or related offenses.
25 2. The state fire marshal and the marshal's paid investigators who have attained proper
26 certification as peace officers pursuant to chapter 590 as approved by the director of the
27 department of public safety shall be deemed to be peace officers and shall notify the local law
28 enforcement agency of the existence of the investigators and shall have the power of arrest for all
